author: Jemillah Bickerton
title: Oz Rock 2016 cancelled: No Hoodoo Gurus or Jebediah for Busselton
text:
The Hoodoo Gurus were due to perform at Oz Rock next year. 
The City of Busselton has confirmed the Oz Rock concert will be a no show for 2016.
It was set to be the event's third appearance in Busselton, with the likes of Jimmy Barnes, Ross Wilson and Diesel previously brought to the town.
The 2016 lineup had already been announced, with Hoodoo Gurus and Jebediah headlining, as well as tickets currently being sold. 
City of Busselton commercial services manager Jenny May said the organisers of Oz Rock had notified the city of the cancellation.
Advertisement "The city remains optimistic that the event will return to the region in 2017," she said.
Organiser Down Under Events has not announced the cancellation on its website or Facebook page.
The Busselton Dunsborough Mail understands the concert was cancelled due to falling ticket sales. 
Controversy hit the inaugural event in 2014 when  a woman reported being sexually assaulted  by a man while attending the festival.
Story from the Busselton Dunsborough Mail
